I"Õ<p><a href="https://blog.pagebakers.nl/2009/01/29/git-ignoring-changes-in-tracked-files/">GIT: ignoring changes in tracked files</a></p>

<blockquote>
  <p>just run the following command on the file or path you want to ignore the changes of:</p>
</blockquote>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>git update-index --assume-unchanged &lt;file&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>

<blockquote>
  <p>If you wanna start tracking changes again run the following command:</p>
</blockquote>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>git update-index --no-assume-unchanged &lt;file&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>
:ET